description.narrative: This activity (CAIPA - Re-supply for ETCs) is a component of Ebola Treatment Centres in Sierra Leone reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Humanitarian assistance' and a budget of £14,926,496. This component benefits Sierra Leone, and works in the following sector(s): Material relief assistance and services , Relief co-ordination and support services. , with the following implementing partners: International Procurement Agency. The start date is 18-12-2014 and the end date is 30-09-2015.
